  .card-box.tweet
    a(href="spacing.html").author
      img.avatar(src='https://img.icons8.com/color/48/000000/full-image.png')
      span.name Spacing-Helper
      span.username  @each loop
    .content
      P
      p This .scss loop will create "margin helpers" and "padding helpers" for use in your web projects.
      p It will generate several classes such as:
      p .m-r-10 which gives margin-right 10 pixels.
      p .m-r-15 gives MARGIN to the RIGHT 15 pixels.
      p .m-t-15 gives MARGIN to the TOP 15 pixels and so on.
      p .p-b-5 gives PADDING to the BOTTOM of 5 pixels
      p .p-l-40 gives PADDING to the LEFT of 40 pixels
      p The first letter is "m" or "p" for MARGIN or PADDING
      p Second letter is "t", "b", "l", or "r" for TOP, BOTTOM, LEFT, or RIGHT
      p Third letter is the number of spacing in pixels. Adjust the amounts generated by editing the $spaceamounts variable below.

    .actions
      span.fa.fa-reply
      span.fa.fa-retweet
      span.fa.fa-heart
